  "prompt": "What marks are required in the IISER aptitude test in order to get admission in any of the IISERs? Also, what rank in the JEE (Advanced) is good enough?",
  "response": "For IISER admission, typically:\n\nIISER Aptitude Test (IAT) Cutoffs:\n- Generally, candidates scoring around 60-70% are considered for admission\n- Exact cutoffs vary each year and by specific IISER\n- Top 10-15% performers have higher chances of selection\n\nJEE (Advanced) Rank Considerations:\n- Ranks within top 5,000-10,000 are usually considered good\n- Many successful candidates are in the top 2,000-3,000 ranks\n- Lower ranked candidates can still get admission based on IAT performance\n\nImportant Notes:\n- Performance in both IAT and JEE (Advanced) is considered\n- State quota and category-wise reservations also play a role\n- Cutoffs can differ for different IISER campuses\n- Candidates should check official IISER admission websites for most current criteria\n\nRecommendation:\n- Aim for a good score in both IAT and JEE (Advanced)\n- Prepare thoroughly for both exams\n- Keep track of official IISER admission notifications\n\nThese are general guidelines, and actual admission depends on specific year's criteria.",
